Dublin (IRL)

Montpellier (FRA) ->
As mentionned before,
I had the chance to
visit Dublin. I, even,
did it twice!
Now, I want to live in it.
Dublin is one of the european
cities that pleased me.
Secondary Schools
Lodève (FRA)
Lycée Joseph Vallot
I had to find new friends when I moved from Paris.
I made some along the way to my "baccalauréat".
I obtained it with honors. My cursus was a science
cursus and my speciality mathematics. I also get the
maximum grade at my mathematics exam at my
"baccalauréat".
Swiss Army Knife Jobs
Many (FRA)
Many
3 years
At the age of sixteen, I worked every weekend
as a greengrocer in the weekly market. It lasted
for a year. After that, I also worked during summers
as supermarket baker, janitor in the same bulding I
was doing my PhD (that's funny) and campsite
assistant manager. I develop a large range of skills
including the ability to work in a team as well
as being autonomous for example.
BSc: Psychology & MIASHS
Montpellier (FRA)
Paul-Valéry University
3 years
I studied two differents bachelors simultanely.
The first one MIASHS concerned mathematics,
computing with a minor about human and
social sciences. I choose psychology.
At the end of my first class of social psychology,
even if inscriptions were closed, I send an email
to the university president to allow me to do a
double cursus.
Three years later, I succefully granted both.
Even better, I suceeded with honor in MIASHS.
Internship : Database Architect
Montpellier (FRA)
Namaé Concept
2 months
At the end of my third year of the MIASHS bachelor.,
I had to do an intership. With a friend of mine who
studied with me we knocked at every startup doors
in Montpellier. Finally, we were choose by Namaé
Concept to construct a brand new database from
existing data and data that was had to scrap from
internet. Namaé Concept was a startup about
companies naming. My friend and me did what
was asked, a brand new database containing all
words from many languages or culturs, all US
companies names since the 18th century.
Trip alone across Europe
14 countries
2.5 months
At the end of my second year of double bachelor,
I choose to not work another summer as I did
during all the previous and take a little money,
my backpack and got ready to hitchhike and take
buses. It was a truly formative time for myself. I got
confident to express myself in english and had to
overcome many unexpected situations along the
way. I planned my 14 countries trip before to visit
many capitals. Some of thoses cities felt like home.
Dublin was one of them.
Pilou's Adoption, Woof!
Montpellier (FRA)
We were a foster home for dogs during a year with
my flatmates. We foster five dogs and Pilou was the
third one to came. After few months, I decided to
adopt him. It is a great responsability to have a dog
as it never gets autonomous.
He was a year old when he first
came. We celebrated his third
birthday few weeks back.
Pilou
Sandwich Course: Fraud Data Analyst
La Défense (FRA)
SNCF
1 year
The MIASHS MSc was a sandwich course cursus.
Half of the time I was at the SNCF 2nd HQ in La
Défense near Paris. The other half of the time I was
at the university learning. At the SNCF, I was
responsible to stop the fraud the SNCF suffer at
selling train tickets trough the remote customer
service (phone). I had no supervision in terms of
techniques and proposed solutions that would
have take years to be according to my supervisors.
Humanly speaking, it was great but my competences
were use so little that I decided to leave after a year.
MSc: MIASHS
Montpellier (FRA)
Paul-Valéry University
2 years
The MIASHS MSc was supposed to be complete
with work experiences. I worked at the SNCF and
at the LIRMM. The MSc did not contain a minor
as the BSc did. I had to say goobye to psycholgy.
It did not stop my motivation of course and I
succeded with honors. I always though that I will
work directly after my MSc but I finally choose to
stay 3 more years in Montpellier to perform a PhD.
One of the main reason of this decision is that I felt
that I knew too litlle about deep-learning at this time
and wanted to use and understand neural networks.
Startup and research
Montpellier (FRA)
LIRMM
My second year of MIASHS MSc I choose to
try to launch my own startup alone. A cruel fail due
to my lack of realism about the feasibility of my
project alone. One of my professor offers me the
opportunity of an intership in research. I instantanelly
loved it. During the day I worked as a research
engineer and during the evening I was working as a
Deliveroo rider to pay my studies. At the end of this
internship, the team I was working with including
my professor proposed me the PhD position that
was oppening.
1 year - 3 months
Conférence EGC (French)
Two first publications
Brussels (BEL)
I presented two papers about EBBE-Text
(Explanations By Boundary Exploration applied to
Textual data). It was not really my first papers as I
published an extended version of a paper during
my LIRMM internship. The first EBBE-Text paper was
a long article which describe how EBBE-Text explains
binary classification of a neural network classifier.
The second paper was a demonstration during the
conference. I was awarded the best demonstration
paper of the conference.
Teacher
Béziers (FRA)
University of Montpellier
3 years
At the very beginning of my PhD, I started to teach
computer classes to first year student. I did it for a
total of 192 hours in three years. I teach javascript,
PHP, SQL to first and second years. According to
my collegues, students I was good at it. I invest
myself completly in it because I loved it.
Moved to South of France
When my mother get back in touch with her
youth love, her, my sister our first dog Sandy and
me move to south of France.
I went from a Paris suburb to a house isolated
from everything.
Maisons-Alfort (FRA) ->
Lodève (FRA)

text.tspan: My thesis
Montpellier (FRA)
University of Montpellier
Abstract:
Deep neural networks have shown, over the last
decade, a significant increase in performance for
many predictive tasks. Nevertheless, their
complexity (large number of trainable parameters)
make them appear as black boxes to the users, with
the latter having difficulties in the understanding of
their predictions. Recently, the interest of the
scientific community in interpreting their predictions
is significantly increased. In this thesis, we focus on
data visualization techniques that leverage [...]
First International Paper (Q1)
IEEE TVCG
Abstract:
While neural networks (NN) have been successfully
applied to many NLP tasks, the way they function is
often difficult to interpret. In this article, we focus
on binary text classification via NNs and propose a
new tool, which includes a visualization of the
decision boundary and the distances of data
elements to this boundary. This tool increases the
interpretability of NN. Our approach uses two
innovative views: (1) an overview of the text
representation space and (2) a local view allowing
data exploration around the decision boundary for
various localities of this representation space. [...]
